WEBVTT

00:03.550 --> 00:05.070
ANNOUNCER:
<i>On the last episode of</i> Soap,

00:05.071 --> 00:06.572
<i>Billy decided</i>
<i>to leave the Sunnies,</i>

00:06.573 --> 00:07.573
<i>only Reverend Sung</i>
<i>decided he couldn't</i>

00:07.574 --> 00:10.075
<i>and is keeping him</i>
<i>against his will.</i>

00:10.076 --> 00:13.078
<i>Burt decided to find out</i>
<i>if he really saw a spaceship,</i>

00:13.079 --> 00:15.080
<i>which might've been</i>
<i>a bad decision</i>

00:15.081 --> 00:16.081
<i>because he saw another one</i>

00:16.082 --> 00:18.584
<i>and then vanished into thin air.</i>

00:18.585 --> 00:22.588
<i>And Jessica told Chester and</i>
<i>Donahue she made a decision</i>

00:22.589 --> 00:26.091
<i>only she didn't tell them</i>
<i>which one she decided on.</i>

00:26.092 --> 00:27.593
<i>Confused? You won't be</i>

00:27.594 --> 00:31.097
<i>if you decide to watch</i>
<i>this episode of...</i> Soap.

00:34.601 --> 00:35.601
[♪]

00:35.602 --> 00:38.103
<i>This is the story</i>
<i>of two sisters,</i>

00:38.104 --> 00:40.606
<i>Jessica Tate</i>

00:40.607 --> 00:42.608
<i>and Mary Campbell.</i>

00:42.609 --> 00:46.111
<i>These are the Tates.</i>

00:46.112 --> 00:50.115
<i>And these are Campbell's.</i>

00:50.116 --> 00:53.119
<i>And this is...</i> Soap.

00:58.625 --> 01:00.626
You son of a...

01:00.627 --> 01:02.127
Oh!

01:02.128 --> 01:04.129
[CLAMORING]

01:12.639 --> 01:16.141
ANNOUNCER:
<i>We begin this episode where we left off,</i>

01:16.142 --> 01:20.145
<i>with Jessica about to</i>
<i>announce her decision.</i>

01:20.146 --> 01:21.647
I want you to know

01:21.648 --> 01:25.150
that I really never meant
to hurt either of you.

01:25.151 --> 01:28.153
But it seems that in order to be
with the man I love,

01:28.154 --> 01:30.656
I have to hurt
the other man I love.

01:30.657 --> 01:33.158
So I just don't know
what else to do.

01:33.159 --> 01:36.161
Does this mean
you've made a decision?

01:36.162 --> 01:38.163
Yes, I have.

01:38.164 --> 01:41.167
I have chosen one of you.

01:47.674 --> 01:49.174
Well?

01:49.175 --> 01:52.678
Well, I'm afraid one of you
is going to be hurt.

01:52.679 --> 01:54.680
Well, we know that Jess.

01:54.681 --> 01:56.181
Oh, it's so hard.

01:56.182 --> 01:57.683
It's not easy for us.

01:57.684 --> 02:00.686
Just say the name, Jess.

02:00.687 --> 02:01.688
Okay.

02:03.189 --> 02:04.190
I will.

02:07.694 --> 02:09.195
It's...

02:11.197 --> 02:12.698
It's...

02:12.699 --> 02:14.199
Ohhh...

02:14.200 --> 02:15.701
I can't.

02:15.702 --> 02:17.704
Me, Jess, me.

02:20.206 --> 02:23.208
Jessica, I assure you
whoever loses will take it well.

02:23.209 --> 02:26.712
Absolutely. If I lose,
and I don't expect to,

02:26.713 --> 02:28.213
I will remain perfectly calm.

02:28.214 --> 02:30.215
I will not eat my heart out.

02:30.216 --> 02:32.217
Why not? You eat
everything else.

02:32.218 --> 02:33.719
Shh, shh, Chester, Chester.

02:33.720 --> 02:36.221
Jess, don't worry, if I lose,
and I don't expect to,

02:36.222 --> 02:39.224
I'll take it like a man.
A very little man.

02:39.225 --> 02:41.727
Gentlemen, stop that, please.

02:41.728 --> 02:43.729
We will be gentlemen, Jess.

02:43.730 --> 02:47.232
I'll tell you what I'll do.
I'll write it down.

02:47.233 --> 02:49.234
Because I just...
I cannot say it.

02:49.235 --> 02:52.238
I just... I cannot.
I cannot say it.

02:55.742 --> 03:00.746
All right, I will put "yes"
on one sheet of paper

03:00.747 --> 03:02.748
and "no" on the other.

03:02.749 --> 03:06.251
And then I will put one
in each envelope,

03:06.252 --> 03:07.753
and I will hand them out.

03:07.754 --> 03:11.257
All right.
Okay.

03:11.758 --> 03:13.759
I'm ready.

03:13.760 --> 03:16.763
I will now hand out
the envelopes.

03:18.264 --> 03:19.765
Isn't this fun?

03:19.766 --> 03:22.768
It's just like
the Academy Awards.

03:22.769 --> 03:25.271
And the winner is...

03:27.000 --> 03:33.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:35.782 --> 03:37.783
[LAUGHING]

03:37.784 --> 03:38.784
I'm so happy!

03:38.785 --> 03:40.786
Ohhh!

03:40.787 --> 03:43.288
Ohhh!

03:43.289 --> 03:45.290
Oh, God!

03:45.291 --> 03:47.292
Ohhh!

03:47.293 --> 03:51.296
Take it like a man,
you fat bull!

03:51.297 --> 03:53.298
Just one minute, please,
let me see.

03:53.299 --> 03:55.801
Did I...?
Did I do it wrong?

03:55.802 --> 03:57.302
Ohhh!

03:57.303 --> 03:59.805
I'm so sorry.

04:00.807 --> 04:03.309
Oh! Oh! Oh!

04:04.310 --> 04:06.311
No!

04:06.312 --> 04:09.815
No! No! No!
Give it to me.

04:09.816 --> 04:11.317
[GASPING]

04:12.318 --> 04:14.319
[SOBBING]

04:14.320 --> 04:15.821
[LAUGHING]

04:15.822 --> 04:16.822
Mmm-mwah!

04:25.331 --> 04:26.331
Is that a "no"?

04:26.332 --> 04:27.332
Yes.

04:27.333 --> 04:28.834
Did you mean a "no" there?

04:28.835 --> 04:30.335
Yes.

04:30.336 --> 04:31.837
That's what I thought.

04:31.838 --> 04:33.839
Then I...
I better leave.

04:33.840 --> 04:36.842
I respect your decision.

04:36.843 --> 04:40.847
I hate it, but I respect it.
I'll see myself to the door.

04:44.350 --> 04:45.351
[SOBS]

04:54.861 --> 04:56.862
Chester, he died.

04:56.863 --> 04:59.865
No, he didn't die,
Jessica, he fainted.

04:59.866 --> 05:01.366
Donahue!

05:01.367 --> 05:03.368
Donahue, you fool.
[GROANING]

05:03.369 --> 05:04.870
Get up on your little feet.

05:04.871 --> 05:06.873
Oh, I'm so sorry.

05:08.875 --> 05:10.876
My legs just won't...

05:10.877 --> 05:13.379
Oh, goodness' sakes.

05:14.380 --> 05:17.883
Oh, I...
I feel nauseous too.

05:19.886 --> 05:23.388
Here we go.
Jess...

05:23.389 --> 05:26.391
Just get up on your feet.
Here. Come right over here.

05:26.392 --> 05:27.893
There, sit down.

05:27.894 --> 05:29.895
[MOANING]

05:29.896 --> 05:32.397
And now if I could
just spend the night,

05:32.398 --> 05:33.899
in the morning,
I'll be all right.

05:33.900 --> 05:36.902
Well, of course, poor baby.

05:36.903 --> 05:39.404
Forget it, I'll carry
him to his car.

05:39.405 --> 05:40.405
No!

05:40.406 --> 05:42.407
I'm too weak to drive!

05:42.408 --> 05:44.910
No, no!
Jess, no!

05:44.911 --> 05:46.411
You don't have to drive.

05:46.412 --> 05:48.914
You can stay here
until you feel better.

05:48.915 --> 05:49.915
Thank you, Jessica.

05:49.916 --> 05:51.918
Sorry, fat boy.

05:53.419 --> 05:55.921
[♪]

06:06.933 --> 06:07.934
[HOOTS]

06:12.939 --> 06:14.439
[WHIMPERS]

06:14.440 --> 06:17.442
Stay... calm.

06:17.443 --> 06:20.445
Stay calm. Just think.
Stay calm here.

06:20.446 --> 06:22.948
I'll just analyze the situation.

06:26.452 --> 06:28.954
One of three things
is going on here.

06:31.457 --> 06:33.959
Either I'm dreaming
I'm on a spaceship,

06:33.960 --> 06:35.460
or...

06:35.461 --> 06:38.463
I'm on a spaceship...

06:38.464 --> 06:39.965
or...

06:39.966 --> 06:41.467
I'm crazy.

06:44.470 --> 06:45.470
Ha! I'm dreaming.

06:45.471 --> 06:48.473
[LAUGHS]

06:48.474 --> 06:49.475
I'm in a dream!

06:51.978 --> 06:55.480
This is what happens
when you eat pizza in bed, huh.

06:55.481 --> 06:56.982
Wheep, wheep, wheep!

06:56.983 --> 06:58.483
Whoop, whoop, whoop!

06:58.484 --> 07:00.485
[LAUGHS]

07:00.486 --> 07:03.989
Ah. It's time
to wake up, though.

07:03.990 --> 07:04.991
Wake up, Burt.

07:06.993 --> 07:08.994
[SPEAKS
ALIEN DIALECT]

07:08.995 --> 07:11.997
BURT: Burt. Burt. Hey, Burt.
[SPEAKING ALIEN DIALECT]

07:11.998 --> 07:13.498
Wake up, Burt.
Burt!

07:13.499 --> 07:16.001
Come on, rise and shine, Burt!

07:23.509 --> 07:26.011
[SPEAKING CONTINUES]

07:30.516 --> 07:32.518
Crazy's looking good here.

07:35.521 --> 07:39.024
Oh, sir...
Um...

07:39.025 --> 07:42.027
Hey, pal...
I mean, excuse me,

07:42.028 --> 07:46.531
Uh, <i>señor, pardonnez moi,</i>
<i>por favor.</i>

07:46.532 --> 07:47.532
Uh, where am I?

07:47.533 --> 07:49.534
Just relax,
we will not hurt you.

07:49.535 --> 07:51.036
You're on our spaceship.

07:51.037 --> 07:53.538
Oh, <i>gracias, muchos gracias.</i>

07:53.539 --> 07:56.041
I'm not crazy! I'm not crazy!

07:56.042 --> 07:58.544
I'm on a spaceship!

08:03.049 --> 08:04.549
You speak English?

08:04.550 --> 08:07.052
Of course, we have studied you
Earth people for a long time.

08:07.053 --> 08:08.553
We speak all your languages
fluently.

08:08.554 --> 08:10.555
We read and write most of them.

08:10.556 --> 08:12.057
We also disco.

08:19.065 --> 08:20.565
You guys are... I love this!

08:20.566 --> 08:23.068
I can't wait to get back
to Earth.

08:23.069 --> 08:26.072
Wait till Mary hears this.
She thinks I'm crazy.

08:27.573 --> 08:30.075
Listen, listen, if you guys
are finished here,

08:30.076 --> 08:32.077
I'd like to get going,
but, psh, hey,

08:32.078 --> 08:34.078
let's keep in touch.

08:34.080 --> 08:36.581
I'm afraid we cannot
let you go just yet.

08:36.582 --> 08:37.582
Well why, what do you need?

08:37.582 --> 08:39.583
Another five, 10, 15
minutes, you got it.

08:39.585 --> 08:41.086
Ask me, anything you wanna
know I'll tell you.

08:41.087 --> 08:43.587
If I could be home for
dinner, it would be nice.

08:43.589 --> 08:45.590
I'm afraid you'll not be going
home for dinner.

08:45.591 --> 08:47.592
I won't?

08:47.593 --> 08:48.593
No.

08:49.595 --> 08:51.596
Hey, look, listen, pal.
Now wait a minute.

08:51.597 --> 08:53.598
I gotta go. My wife's
gonna be worried sick here.

08:53.599 --> 08:55.100
No, she will not.

08:55.101 --> 08:57.603
You see, we are sending down
a replica of you.

08:59.105 --> 09:01.106
What? What are you...?
What are you talking about?

09:01.107 --> 09:02.607
While you were unconscious,

09:02.608 --> 09:04.109
we tapped into
your chromosome key.

09:04.110 --> 09:06.111
We can now produce
an exact copy of you.

09:06.112 --> 09:08.613
You made another Burt Campbell?

09:08.614 --> 09:10.615
That is right.
He's your double.

09:10.616 --> 09:12.117
Your wife will never know
he is not you.

09:12.118 --> 09:16.621
My double. Ha-ha, I love it!
This is terrific!

09:16.622 --> 09:17.622
Let me see my double.

09:17.623 --> 09:19.124
Here he is.

09:25.631 --> 09:26.632
She'll know.

09:30.136 --> 09:32.637
Oh, no, you see, he has
not been transformed yet.

09:32.638 --> 09:33.638
He will enter
your duplicate body,

09:33.639 --> 09:35.140
and we will beam him down.

09:35.141 --> 09:37.142
He will look exactly like you.
Your wife will never know.

09:37.143 --> 09:38.643
What do you mean?

09:38.644 --> 09:40.645
You mean Mary's gonna think
that he's really me?

09:40.646 --> 09:42.147
Yes.

09:42.148 --> 09:44.150
[SPEAKING
ALIEN DIALECT]

09:47.653 --> 09:49.654
Why is...? Why is he jumping up
and down like that?

09:49.655 --> 09:51.656
It is nothing.
No, come on.

09:51.657 --> 09:52.657
What's the matter with him?

09:52.658 --> 09:54.159
He is just a little excited.

09:54.160 --> 09:55.660
Yeah, but about what?

09:55.661 --> 09:57.663
Going down to Earth.
Living in your house.

10:00.166 --> 10:01.666
Oh, he's... No, wait.

10:01.667 --> 10:03.669
You're not gonna let him...

10:06.172 --> 10:07.672
I mean he's not gonna...

10:07.673 --> 10:09.675
Sleep with your wife?
[GROANS]

10:14.680 --> 10:17.182
Why do you think
he's jumping up and down?

10:18.684 --> 10:21.687
He has not had sex
in 2000 years.

10:23.189 --> 10:25.691
[♪]

10:33.699 --> 10:35.700
Happy anniversary, Jodie.

10:35.701 --> 10:37.202
Ohhh...
[LAUGHS]

10:40.206 --> 10:43.208
You're the best thing
I ever had in my life.

10:43.209 --> 10:44.210
And you in mine.

10:47.713 --> 10:49.715
Three months together.
Mm.

10:50.716 --> 10:52.717
How come you have four candles?

10:52.718 --> 10:54.720
Well, I wanna
throw away the box.

11:00.226 --> 11:02.227
You know, I think
relationships are better

11:02.228 --> 11:05.231
when there's no sex
to screw things up.

11:08.734 --> 11:09.735
[DOORBELL RINGS]

11:14.240 --> 11:15.240
Hi, Jodie.

11:15.241 --> 11:17.243
Remember me?

11:19.745 --> 11:20.745
Mrs. David.

11:20.746 --> 11:21.746
Hi.

11:21.747 --> 11:22.747
Oh!

11:22.748 --> 11:24.249
Hello there.

11:24.250 --> 11:28.253
This is Alice, Alice this is
Mrs. David, Carol's mother.

11:28.254 --> 11:29.254
Oh.

11:29.255 --> 11:32.758
So... you're not
a homo anymore?

11:34.760 --> 11:37.262
Jodie was my first homo.

11:37.263 --> 11:41.266
Uh, no, Mrs. David.
I'm still a homo.

11:41.267 --> 11:43.268
But you're with a girl.

11:43.269 --> 11:45.270
Well, we're both homos.

11:45.271 --> 11:47.272
[LAUGHS]

11:47.273 --> 11:48.273
What's so funny?

11:48.274 --> 11:50.776
A girl homo.

11:52.278 --> 11:54.779
There's no such thing
as a girl homo.

11:54.780 --> 11:56.781
Yes, there is.

11:56.782 --> 11:58.283
A girl homo?

11:58.284 --> 12:00.285
What do they call 'em, homettes?

12:00.286 --> 12:01.287
[LAUGHS]

12:04.290 --> 12:05.290
Oh, Jodie.

12:05.291 --> 12:06.791
I got a little surprise for you.

12:06.792 --> 12:08.793
What is it?
I'll bring it in.

12:08.794 --> 12:10.295
"Homettes." "Homettes."

12:13.299 --> 12:14.800
Ta-dah!

12:18.304 --> 12:19.304
Is that...?

12:19.305 --> 12:20.806
Your daughter.

12:22.308 --> 12:26.812
Carol wanted you to see her.
That's why I made the trip.

12:31.317 --> 12:32.438
[SOFTLY] That's my daughter.

12:34.320 --> 12:36.321
She don't do much.

12:36.322 --> 12:40.325
JODIE:
Would you look at her?

12:40.326 --> 12:43.328
Now, Jodie, I don't like
to impose or anything,

12:43.329 --> 12:46.331
but I'm a little afraid
of staying in a hotel

12:46.332 --> 12:47.832
with all the raping
and murdering

12:47.833 --> 12:49.834
that goes on in this city.

12:49.835 --> 12:51.836
The cab driver told me

12:51.837 --> 12:53.338
that over half the men
in New York

12:53.339 --> 12:55.841
are either junkies,
muggers or lawyers.

12:57.843 --> 12:59.844
Mrs. David, you're welcome
to stay here with us.

12:59.845 --> 13:01.346
Alice?
Sure.

13:01.347 --> 13:03.348
Oh, I sure do appreciate it.

13:03.349 --> 13:04.849
Do you wanna hold her?

13:04.850 --> 13:05.850
[INHALES]

13:05.851 --> 13:07.352
Oh, I don't know how.

13:07.353 --> 13:08.353
Oh, it's simple.

13:08.354 --> 13:09.854
You just pick her up

13:09.855 --> 13:13.858
the way you pick up
a frozen turkey at the market.

13:13.859 --> 13:14.859
Go ahead.

13:14.860 --> 13:16.361
Watch her head.
Okay.

13:16.362 --> 13:20.365
See?
Oh, she likes you.

13:20.366 --> 13:22.867
[ALL COO]

13:22.868 --> 13:24.369
That's right.

13:24.370 --> 13:26.872
Now you cradle her in your arms.

13:30.376 --> 13:32.377
There you are.

13:32.378 --> 13:34.879
I'm afraid I'm gonna drop her.

13:34.880 --> 13:37.382
Oh, I was dropped
when I was a baby.

13:42.388 --> 13:45.890
That's why I can't do math.
Ha ha!

13:45.891 --> 13:48.393
Well, how do you like her?

13:48.394 --> 13:50.395
She's terrific.

13:50.396 --> 13:52.397
This is so strange, though.

13:52.398 --> 13:54.399
Oh, she's your daughter.

13:54.400 --> 13:55.400
It's my daughter.

13:55.401 --> 13:58.403
Do you believe it?
It's my daughter?

13:58.404 --> 14:00.905
This is my daughter.

14:00.906 --> 14:01.906
What's her name?

14:01.907 --> 14:03.408
Her name's Wendy.

14:04.910 --> 14:06.911
Wendy.

14:06.912 --> 14:09.414
It's very nice
to meet you, Wendy.

14:10.916 --> 14:12.917
Well, if I'm gonna stay here,

14:12.918 --> 14:14.919
I better go get
my things out of the cab.

14:14.920 --> 14:16.421
You left the cab
waiting all this time?

14:16.422 --> 14:19.424
Yes. Your fare'll be more
than your trip from Texas.

14:19.425 --> 14:21.426
MRS. DAVID:
Oh, my goodness.

14:21.427 --> 14:23.928
[WHISPERS] Hey.

14:23.929 --> 14:26.931
Hey. Hey, Wendy. Hmm?

14:26.932 --> 14:29.434
Hey, hello.

14:29.435 --> 14:32.937
You look just like me,
you know that?

14:32.938 --> 14:35.940
Well, you should.
You're my kid. Hmm?

14:35.941 --> 14:38.943
You got big brown eyes and...

14:38.944 --> 14:41.446
cute little nose...

14:41.447 --> 14:42.947
chin.

14:42.948 --> 14:44.449
You have fingers.

14:46.452 --> 14:48.453
And fingernails.

14:48.454 --> 14:49.954
Ohhh...

14:49.955 --> 14:53.958
Hey, you sure
are pretty. Hmm?

14:53.959 --> 14:56.461
Even partially bald,
you're gorgeous.

14:59.965 --> 15:01.466
Yeah.

15:03.969 --> 15:06.971
Oh, boy, Wendy.

15:06.972 --> 15:08.973
It was so much easier

15:08.974 --> 15:12.477
when I didn't know
anything about you.

15:12.478 --> 15:14.979
'Cause now that I've seen you...

15:14.980 --> 15:16.982
and now that I've held you...

15:17.983 --> 15:20.485
I never wanna let you go.
[CRYING]

15:20.486 --> 15:21.486
No.

15:21.487 --> 15:24.989
[CRYING STOPS]
Don't cry. That's it.

15:24.990 --> 15:26.992
[♪]

15:37.503 --> 15:38.503
Morning.

15:38.504 --> 15:41.005
Look at my face, Corinne,
tell me what you see.

15:41.006 --> 15:42.507
You want the truth?

15:42.508 --> 15:46.010
I've got bags under my eyes,
Corinne, big, big bags.

15:46.011 --> 15:49.013
I look like a basset hound,
and it's all your fault.

15:49.014 --> 15:51.516
No, Eunice,
I think it's heredity.

15:51.517 --> 15:53.017
Heredity and, uh...

15:53.018 --> 15:54.519
age.

15:56.522 --> 15:59.524
No, Corinne. It is because I did
not sleep one wink last night,

15:59.525 --> 16:03.027
not one wink because that child
of yours kept crying.

16:03.028 --> 16:04.529
Isn't there something
you can do?

16:04.530 --> 16:07.532
Eunice, he's just an infant.

16:07.533 --> 16:10.034
Well, discipline him,
for God sakes.

16:10.035 --> 16:12.036
I mean the baby cries all night,

16:12.037 --> 16:15.039
and then you and Tim have
a fight and you cry all night,

16:15.040 --> 16:17.041
and then Donahue walks up
and down the halls

16:17.042 --> 16:18.543
and he cries all night.

16:18.544 --> 16:20.545
And then I sit up and get bags.

16:20.546 --> 16:24.549
Donahue, you are not making
an effort to leave the house.

16:24.550 --> 16:27.552
Looking out the window
is not making an effort.

16:27.553 --> 16:29.053
But, listen, I'm trying,

16:29.054 --> 16:32.056
but every time I get
to the front door, I throw up.

16:32.057 --> 16:35.059
If you wouldn't eat,
you wouldn't throw up.

16:35.060 --> 16:37.062
If you wouldn't eat,
you wouldn't get fat.

16:39.064 --> 16:41.065
You turn my stomach.

16:41.066 --> 16:44.069
A plow couldn't turn
your stomach.

16:45.571 --> 16:47.071
Squirrel.

16:47.072 --> 16:48.072
Pinhead.

16:48.073 --> 16:49.574
Bacteria.
Fatty.

16:49.575 --> 16:51.576
Weasel.
Lard bucket!

16:51.577 --> 16:52.578
[BOTH GRUNTING]

16:54.580 --> 16:57.081
Look, everybody,
look who just came.

16:57.082 --> 16:59.083
Benson's back.

16:59.084 --> 17:00.085
Benson!

17:02.588 --> 17:06.590
Okay, okay, okay, that's enough
touching and grabbing. Okay.

17:06.592 --> 17:07.592
Look at that.

17:07.593 --> 17:11.095
Benson comes home and
everybody stops fighting.

17:11.096 --> 17:14.098
Benson walks through the door
and everybody's happy.

17:14.098 --> 17:15.599
Except Benson.

17:16.602 --> 17:17.602
Hi.

17:17.603 --> 17:19.604
Hi. What's...? What's he...?

17:19.605 --> 17:23.107
Oh, no, Detective Donahue's
not really living here.

17:23.108 --> 17:24.108
See, he's just staying here

17:24.108 --> 17:27.612
until he stops passing out
and throwing up.

17:30.115 --> 17:32.617
You chose Chester.
Hmm.

17:32.618 --> 17:34.620
Don't I get to vote?

17:35.621 --> 17:38.122
Oh, welcome back, Bellson.

17:38.123 --> 17:40.625
I'm not back. I'm just here
because we got a problem.

17:40.626 --> 17:42.627
What's the problem?
Billy.

17:42.628 --> 17:45.129
I just came from that church.
Billy's in a lot of trouble.

17:45.130 --> 17:47.131
I think they're keeping him
against his will.

17:47.132 --> 17:49.133
Against his...?
What?

17:49.134 --> 17:50.134
I'll phone the police.

17:50.135 --> 17:51.135
No, I did that already.

17:51.136 --> 17:53.137
You see this can take
a lot of time

17:53.138 --> 17:54.639
what with constitutional
freedoms and everything.

17:54.640 --> 17:56.641
What we have to do
is go in there after him.

17:56.642 --> 17:59.143
Right. I'll go
and check with Ike.

17:59.144 --> 18:02.647
Benson, why are they
keeping him there?

18:02.648 --> 18:04.649
Well, I think
he's being brainwashed.

18:04.650 --> 18:06.150
Oh, my God!
Oh, no.

18:06.151 --> 18:08.653
They say he isn't there,
but I know he is.

18:08.654 --> 18:10.655
Chester, our Billy.

18:10.656 --> 18:12.156
I'll get him out, Jess.

18:12.157 --> 18:14.659
If I have to break in there
myself I'll get him out.

18:14.660 --> 18:16.160
That's what
we're gonna have to do.

18:16.161 --> 18:17.161
Excuse me.

18:17.162 --> 18:19.163
Daddy, you gotta
think of something.

18:19.164 --> 18:20.164
Excuse me, please.

18:20.165 --> 18:21.165
Major.

18:21.166 --> 18:22.667
But I have an idea.

18:22.668 --> 18:24.168
We've gotta get him out
of there.

18:24.169 --> 18:25.670
I can get him out.

18:25.671 --> 18:28.172
Maybe we should call
Channel 7 news.

18:28.173 --> 18:30.675
[OTHERS GRUMBLING]

18:30.676 --> 18:32.678
Attention, damn it!

18:37.182 --> 18:40.184
Now I know sometimes
you don't like to listen to me,

18:40.185 --> 18:41.686
and sometimes
I can understand why,

18:41.687 --> 18:43.688
but you must
all listen to me now.

18:43.689 --> 18:44.690
Major...
Shut up.

18:46.692 --> 18:48.693
Now, look here.

18:48.694 --> 18:50.194
This is the Silver Star.

18:50.195 --> 18:52.196
It was presented to me
by General Patton.

18:52.197 --> 18:54.699
This is a Bronze Star,
I earned two of them.

18:54.700 --> 18:57.702
And... this is the Purple Heart.

18:57.703 --> 19:00.705
Harry Truman pinned that
on me himself.

19:00.706 --> 19:05.710
Now, I know you think
I'm a foolish old man.

19:05.711 --> 19:10.214
And sometimes I am,
but that's my grandson in there.

19:10.215 --> 19:12.216
I got all of these

19:12.217 --> 19:15.219
because I was a good soldier,
I still am.

19:15.220 --> 19:18.222
I can get him out.
I can do it.

19:18.223 --> 19:21.726
So you all had better listen
to this old fool,

19:21.727 --> 19:26.731
because... that's <i>our</i> little boy.

19:26.732 --> 19:30.234
All right, Daddy,
we're listening.

19:30.235 --> 19:32.237
Go ahead, sir,
tell us your plan.

19:33.739 --> 19:35.240
What plan?

19:40.245 --> 19:43.748
MAJOR:
Well, gentlemen, there's the plan.

19:49.254 --> 19:50.755
Any questions?

19:50.756 --> 19:52.256
I don't believe this.

19:52.257 --> 19:55.760
I don't believe that I've
allowed myself to do this.

19:55.761 --> 19:58.262
Donahue, will you stop
complaining.

19:58.263 --> 20:00.765
Benson, I'm not Donahue.

20:02.267 --> 20:03.267
You're not?

20:03.268 --> 20:04.769
No, Benson.

20:04.770 --> 20:07.773
It's amazing,
you all look alike.

20:10.275 --> 20:12.276
Very funny, Benson.

20:12.277 --> 20:14.278
And I want to thank you
personally

20:14.279 --> 20:16.280
for convincing us
to listen to the Major.

20:16.281 --> 20:18.282
Yeah, he said he had a plan.

20:18.283 --> 20:20.785
I didn't know he was gonna form
a basketball team.

20:21.787 --> 20:23.287
We're a man short.

20:23.288 --> 20:25.790
<i>You're</i> a man short.

20:25.791 --> 20:28.292
You're a man fat.

20:28.293 --> 20:29.293
Come on, guys.

20:29.294 --> 20:30.294
Now, colonel,

20:30.295 --> 20:33.297
I want you to climb up
the north wall,

20:33.298 --> 20:34.298
and, Corporal Donahue,

20:34.299 --> 20:36.801
you stay down
with the grappling hook.

20:36.802 --> 20:40.304
Major, could we change places?
Heights make me queasy.

20:40.305 --> 20:42.807
Hey, so far eight different
things have made you queasy.

20:42.808 --> 20:44.809
Why don't you just
stay here and eat?

20:44.810 --> 20:47.812
Why don't you stay here
and grow?

20:47.813 --> 20:48.813
Come on.

20:48.814 --> 20:50.314
Oh, Benson?

20:50.315 --> 20:51.315
Oh, I am so sorry.

20:51.316 --> 20:53.818
I didn't know
you were entertaining.

20:57.823 --> 20:58.823
Jessica.

20:59.825 --> 21:00.826
Jessica, it's me.

21:03.328 --> 21:06.331
Chester, you are not a Negro.

21:08.333 --> 21:12.336
I know that, dear.
We're rescuing Billy.

21:12.337 --> 21:13.838
And then we're all
going downtown

21:13.839 --> 21:15.841
to pick up some white women.

21:20.345 --> 21:23.848
All right now, let's recap.

21:23.849 --> 21:26.852
Good idea. This one is
much too big for me.

21:30.355 --> 21:33.357
Oh, my boys are all
going off to battle,

21:33.358 --> 21:35.359
and I feel so proud.

21:35.360 --> 21:36.861
She's proud.

21:36.862 --> 21:38.863
I'm going off to war
with the Ritz Brothers,

21:38.864 --> 21:40.365
and she's proud.

21:41.867 --> 21:44.368
Chester, I am frightened.

21:44.369 --> 21:47.371
I mean, I know that that's
our little boy in there

21:47.372 --> 21:48.873
and I'm frightened for him.

21:48.874 --> 21:50.875
But I'm frightened for you too.

21:50.876 --> 21:53.377
Don't worry, Jess.
I'll get him back.

21:53.378 --> 21:56.881
I'll bring our son home.
I promise.

22:01.386 --> 22:04.388
All right.
It's almost the zero hour.

22:04.389 --> 22:06.390
Let's synchronize watches.

22:06.391 --> 22:07.391
1:32.

22:07.392 --> 22:09.894
1:47.

22:09.895 --> 22:10.895
6 on the nose.

22:10.896 --> 22:13.398
Close enough.
Move out.

22:19.404 --> 22:20.905
[DOORBELL RINGS]

22:24.409 --> 22:25.910
[DOORBELL RINGS]

22:30.415 --> 22:31.916
[DOORBELL RINGS]

22:32.417 --> 22:33.918
Burt!

22:33.919 --> 22:34.919
Burt!

22:34.920 --> 22:36.421
Ohhh...

22:38.423 --> 22:41.425
I've been so worried.

22:41.426 --> 22:42.426
Where have you been?

22:42.427 --> 22:43.427
Mary?

22:43.428 --> 22:45.429
Oh, never mind.

22:45.430 --> 22:47.932
I thank God you're home.

22:52.437 --> 22:53.938
Oh, Burt.

22:53.939 --> 22:55.440
Burt, I love you.

22:59.444 --> 23:01.445
You must be starving.

23:01.446 --> 23:02.947
I'll get you something to eat.

23:11.456 --> 23:12.957
We'll eat later.

23:15.961 --> 23:17.462
Whoo-hoo-hoo hoo-hooo!

23:27.472 --> 23:29.974
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Has Jessica made the right decision?</i>

23:29.975 --> 23:32.977
<i>Will Donahue ever feel</i>
<i>well enough to leave the house?</i>

23:32.978 --> 23:35.980
<i>Now that Jodie doesn't want</i>
<i>to let his baby daughter go,</i>

23:35.981 --> 23:37.481
<i>is he in for a tug of war?</i>

23:37.482 --> 23:40.484
<i>Will Mary realize that Burt</i>
<i>isn't really Burt?</i>

23:40.485 --> 23:42.486
<i>What's going to happen</i>
<i>to the real Burt?</i>

23:42.487 --> 23:45.990
<i>And after being with</i>
<i>the new Burt, will Mary care?</i>

23:45.991 --> 23:47.491
<i>Will the Major's plan work?</i>

23:47.492 --> 23:49.493
<i>If it doesn't,</i>
<i>can they do</i> The Gong Show?

23:49.494 --> 23:51.495
<i>These questions and many others</i>

23:51.496 --> 23:53.497
<i>will be answered</i>
<i>on the next episode of...</i>

23:53.498 --> 23:54.999
Soap.

23:57.369 --> 23:59.003
[♪]

